The paper discusses the integration of denoisers in compressed sensing reconstruction algorithms, which falls under the category of signal processing and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT is the most likely sub-category. The paper also specifically mentions the use of denoisers for natural images, which suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) may also be a relevant sub-category. The development of the Denoising-based AMP (D-AMP) framework involves machine learning techniques, which could fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of randomized measurements, which is a common technique in matrix completion (cs.MM) and compressed sensing (cs.SI). Therefore, these two sub-categories are also likely to be relevant.
